shop_intro:     
    set data.global.visitedShop true
    "'Shop', the sign outside reads, and that it is."
    clear_dialog
    play sound bell
    "Inside, a hotot rabbit peeks at you *very* briefly when you enter, before returning to her copy of the Anglian Times. The air hangs heavy the grainy sound of Radio Bluehills 'Top of the Bops'."
    "'Shop' sells a range of junk, from run of the mill tat to 'exclusive' 'high quality' counterfeit brands. The important thing is it's cheap."
    clear_dialog
    "Still, there are goods with some value here and there. Various foodstuffs, tools and treats to choose from, and in an exciting twist for breakfast lovers even a few boxes of breakfast cereal sit on the shelf behind the shopkeeper; nutritional value 90% dust, 10% whatever the fuck wheat is."
    jump shop_intro_cereal_menu

shop_intro_cereal_menu:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk lovely talk "Oh me oh my! Special L! We should get some! Nine out of ten foxy milves recommend it!"
        "I'm sorry did Lovely Lady just say <span class='writtenText'>'milves'</span>?":
            talk lovely talk "No."
            talk nasty talk "Yeah she definitely did."
            talk orb talk "She did, yes."
            jump shop_intro_cereal_menu
        "Isn't breakfast cereal a little working class for you, Lovely Lady?":
            talk lovely talk "Tsk! Cereals are rather popular with the aristocracy these days, I'll have you know, and Special L is among the finest."
            jump shop_intro_cereal_menu
        "What's special about Special L?":
            talk lovely talk "It's reinforced with added lead, hence the L. All for health reasons, you see. Most cereals can't boast that."
            if (roll shop_intro_lead_orb orb 20):
                talk orb talk "I'm sorry, it's reinforced with added *what*? Gods, it's little wonder Oceania is overtaking this stupid little island as the foremost world power, what with them not putting lead in all their food and everything."
                talk nasty talk "What the fuck are you talking about, food without lead? Sounds shit, Orb. We love lead."
                talk lovely talk "We love lead! We love lead! Whee!"
                clear_dialog
                talk orb talk "That's the problem, you Anglian's *do* love lead. You should not *love* lead. It's poisonous, Nasty Girl. It's killing you, Lovely Lady."
                talk nasty talk "It's tasty, dipshit. The chicks dig it, asshole."
                talk lovely talk "Ignore Orb, Nasty Girl, it's just bitter of its unrefined palette, if indeed it has one at all."
                talk lovely talk "More to the point, Anglia hardly became the world's leading exporter of lead on a whim!"
                clear_dialog
                talk lovely talk "Indeed, it is our moral duty as the protégés of Saint Dawnsight to enlighten the uncivilised masses abroad with the oh so precious carbon treasure our hard-working miners hoist from the depths!"
                talk nasty talk "Enlighten them with lead! Yeah, what she said! Fuck you Orb!"
                talk orb talk "Oh my gods, Ghost, ply me out of your chest cavity with a spatula and let me die, I'm fucking begging you."
            else:
                wait 1000
            jump shop_intro_cereal_menu
        "Exciting stuff, Lovely Lady. <span class='prompt'>[[MOVE ON]]</span>":
            jump shop_intro_smoking_menu

shop_intro_smoking_menu:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk nasty talk "Anyway, forget breakfast cereal, this shop sells Östro brand Oestradiol Cigarettes. A smooth minty taste with a satisfying warm sparkle. Östro. Guaranteed to leave you satisfied. BUY SOME TODAY"
        "Is smoking oestradiol safe?":
            talk orb talk "It's banned in 1954, and then relegalised again in 1998 under *heavy* regulation, if that answers your question."
            talk nasty talk "They couldn't hack the heat."
            talk orb talk "If heat is slang for lung cancer, yes."
            talk lovely talk "I simple use an oestrohookah, the classy, *healthy* alternative."
            talk orb talk "Marginally better for you, I suppose, in the same way having a piano dropped on your skull from above is marginally better for you than having a church organ dropped on your skull from above."
            jump shop_intro_smoking_menu
        "What's so good about Östro cigarettes compared to other leading brands, Nasty Girl? I want to ensure sure we're making an informed purchase."
            choice:
                talk nasty talk "More smoke."
                "You're telling me we can get ourselves more smoke with Östro brand cigarettes than with other competing brands? That bops.":
                    talk orb talk "There isn't more smoke, it's just more visible."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk orb talk "The manufacturer uses dye to make it darker, and thus more noticeable, so that people like Nasty Girl think <span class='writtenText'>'Wow so much smoke!'</span>."
                        "That also bops, I think?":
                            choice:
                                talk orb talk "The dye is poisonous."
                                "That doesn't bop.":
                                    choice:
                                        talk orb talk "But it does make the cigarettes more affordable."
                                        "That bops.":
                                            choice:
                                                talk orb talk "But only because half the cigarette is taken up with a cheap filter, to stop the poison killing you instantly."
                                                "That doesn't bop.":
                                                    talk nasty talk "Mhm yess mhm very interesting, Orb, many good points on both sides."
                                                    clear_dialog
                                                    choice:
                                                        talk nasty talk "Can we just buy some fucking cigarettes now?"
                                                        "On balance I think Östro brand Oestradiol Cigarettes bop, we can buy some, Nasty Girl.":
                                                            talk nasty talk "Awoooo! Reason and logic prevail!"
                                                            talk orb talk "Sigh. Just make sure I'm not still inside your body when brain starts to spongeify, will you Ghost?"
                                                        "On balance I think Östro brand Oestradiol Cigarettes do not bop, I think we'll pass, Nasty Girl.":
                                                            talk nasty talk "Fuck you. Brain cuck."
            jump shop_intro_smoking_menu
        "I'll think about it. <span class='prompt'>[[MOVE ON]]</span>":
            talk nasty talk "Fuck thinking, you fucking brain cuck. Buy some cigarettes."
            jump shop_intro_outro
        "Sorry Nasty Girl, but smokers are jokers. <span class='prompt'>[[MOVE ON]]</span>":
            talk nasty talk "Kill yourself."
            jump shop_intro_outro

shop_intro_outro:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk orb talk "Anyhow, the only thing we *really* need to buy right now is some nails."
        "Nails.":
            talk orb talk "Yes Ghost, <span class='writtenText'>'nails'</span>."
    clear_dialog
    jump shop_menu